==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peyers glands
<hw>Pey"er's glands`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[So called from <person>J.
K. <etsep>Peyer</etsep></person>, who described them in 1677.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Patches of lymphoid nodules, in the walls of the
small intestiness; agminated glands; -- called also <altname>Peyer's
patches</altname>. In typhoid fever they become the seat of ulcers which
are regarded as the characteristic organic lesion of that
disease.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peytrel</ent>⟦br⟧
